definition.value: A department of Colombia. It is in the south-west of the country, bordering Ecuador and Peru. Its capital is Mocoa.
A city, and the capital city of the San Pedro Partido in Buenos Aires Province, Argentina.
A populated place. A city in the northeast of the province of Buenos Aires, Argentina. It lies on the western shore of the Parana River, 90 km from Buenos Aires.

A province in northeastern Argentina, part of the Gran Chaco Region. Its northeast end touches Asuncion, Paraguay, and borders the provinces of Chaco and Salta to its south and west, respectively. The capital is Formosa.
A province of Argentina, located in the center of the country. It is divided into 26 departments. Its capital, Cordoba, is the second largest city in the country.

A province of Argentina, located in the northwest of the country. Neighbouring provinces are (clockwise, from the north): Salta, Tucuman, Santiago del Estero, Cordoba, and La Rioja. To the west it borders Chile.
A city located near the geographical center of Argentina, in the foothills of the Sierras Chicas on the Suquia River, about 700 km northwest from Buenos Aires. It is the capital of Cordoba Province.
A province of Argentina, located in the western part of the country. Neighbouring provinces are, moving clockwise from the north, La Rioja, San Luis and Mendoza. It borders Chile on the west.

A province of Argentina, located in the northwest of the country. Neighboring provinces are from the east clockwise Formosa, Chaco, Santiago del Estero, Tucuman and Catamarca. It also surrounds Jujuy. To the north it borders Bolivia and Paraguay and to the west lies Chile.
One of the provinces of Argentina and is located in the west of the country. Neighboring provinces are from the north clockwise Catamarca, Cordoba, San Luis and San Juan.

A province of Argentina, located in the Pampas in the centre of the country. Limita al oeste con la provincia de Mendoza, al sur con el rio Colorado que la separa de la provincia de Rio Negro, al este con la de Buenos Aires y al norte con San Luis y Cordoba. Los limites de las provincias de La Pampa, Rio Negro, Mendoza y Neuquen, se encuentran en un punto, en la interseccion del rio Colorado con la traza erronea del meridiano X Oeste de Buenos Aires.
A province of Argentina, located in the southern part of the country, in Patagonia. It borders Chubut province to the north, and Chile to the west and south. To the east is the Atlantic Ocean.

A province of Argentina, located in the center-east of the country. Neighboring provinces are from the north clockwise Chaco, Corrientes, Entre Rios, Buenos Aires, Cordoba, and Santiago del Estero. Together with Cordoba and Entre Rios the province is part of the economico-political association known as the Center Region.
A province of Argentina located near the geographical center of the country. Neighboring provinces are, from the north clockwise, La Rioja, Cordoba, La Pampa, Mendoza and San Juan.
The largest city in the province of Santa Fe, Argentina. It is located 300 km northwest of Buenos Aires, on the western shore of the Parana River.
A province of Argentina, located in the north of the country. Neighbouring provinces are from the north clockwise Salta, Chaco, Santa Fe, Cordoba, Catamarca and Tucuman.
Una ciudad argentina, capital de la provincia de Tierra del Fuego, Antartida e Islas del Atlantico Sur.
The capital and the largest city in the State of Goias. It is also the largest city de facto in the Central-Western Region of Brazil.

The state capital of Ceara, located in northeastern Brazil. To the north of the city lies the Atlantic Ocean; to the south are the Municipalities of Pacatuba, Eusebio, Maracanau and Itaitinga; to the east is the Municipality of Aquiraz and the Atlantic Ocean; and to the west is the Municipality of Caucaia.
A city located in the northern region of the State of the Parana, Brazil.
The capital city of Rio Grande do Norte, a north eastern state in Brazil. Natal lies on the Atlantic Ocean, at the mouth of the Potengi river.
A Brazilian city of the Vale do Aco metropolitan area in the State of Minas Gerais.
The largest of the nine constituent departments of Bolivia.
One of the nine departments of Bolivia.
A department of Bolivia.
A department of Bolivia.
A department in Bolivia. Its capital is the city of Oruro.
A department in Bolivia. It is located in south eastern Bolivia bordering Argentina to the south and Paraguay to the east.
One of the nine departments of Bolivia.
A department of Bolivia located in the center south. It borders on the departments of Cochabamba, Tarija, Potosi, and Santa Cruz.
A northeastern department of Bolivia, in the lowlands region of the country.
A populated place.

The capital of Al Isma'iliyah Governorate. It is located on the west bank of the Suez Canal, approximately half way between Port Said to the north and Suez to the south. The Canal widens at that point to include Timsah, one of the Bitter Lakes linked by the Canal.
